data.text:
Full Name: Björk Guðmundsdóttir

Profession: Singer

Biography: Famous initially as the lead singer of the alternative rock band "The Sugarcubes", she has developed an eclectic and avant-garde musical style over her three-decade solo career that incorporates a range of musical styles.

Critics have praised her innovative approach to singing and song composition, and some believe she is the most important musician of her generation.

Born: November 21, 1965

Birthplace: Reykjavik, Iceland

Age: 58 years old
